 Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">255</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":255,\"repo\":\"bjodah/chempy\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Python package useful for chemistry (mainly physical/inorganic/analytical chemistry)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-19T09:36:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Others</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/girke-lab/eiR\">eiR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/girke-lab/eiR\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"girke-lab/eiR\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Accelerated similarity searching of small molecules</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-17T18:08:00.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Machine Learning</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Mariewelt/OpenChem\">OpenChem</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Mariewelt/OpenChem\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">372</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":372,\"repo\":\"Mariewelt/OpenChem\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - OpenChem is a deep learning toolkit for Computational Chemistry with PyTorch backend.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-16T06:57:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Molecular Dynamics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ks.uiuc.edu/Research/namd/\">NAMD</a> - a parallel molecular dynamics code designed for high-performance simulation of large biomolecular systems.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-13T09:49:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Command Line Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://meilerlab.org/index.php/bclcommons/show/b_apps_id/1\">BCL::Commons</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-10T09:48:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Others</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/MolSSI/cookiecutter-cms\">Cookiecutter for Computational Molecular Sciences</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/MolSSI/cookiecutter-cms\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">207</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":207,\"repo\":\"MolSSI/cookiecutter-cms\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Python-centric Cookiecutter for Molecular Computational Chemistry Packages by <a href=\"https://molssi.org/\">MolSSL</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-26T03:13:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>See Also</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://molssi.org/software-search/\">MolSSI Molecular Software Database</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-26T03:13:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Courses</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Mishima-syk/py4chemoinformatics\">Python for chemoinformatics</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Mishima-syk/py4chemoinformatics\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">144</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":144,\"repo\":\"Mishima-syk/py4chemoinformatics\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-26T02:19:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Courses</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dasher.wustl.edu/chem430/\">Simulation in Chemistry and Biochemistry</a> - by Dr. <a href=\"https://dasher.wustl.edu/\">Jay Ponder</a>, a professor from WashU St.Louis.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-20T01:49:38.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Courses</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dasher.wustl.edu/chem478/\">Molecular modeling course</a> - by Dr. <a href=\"https://dasher.wustl.edu/\">Jay Ponder</a>, a professor from WashU St.Louis.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-23T15:52:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Virtual Machine</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://chembl.blogspot.com/2015/07/mychembl-20-has-landed.html\">myChEMBL</a> - A version of ChEMBL built using Open Source software (Ubuntu, PostgreSQL, RDKit)</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-13T02:41:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/chimera/\">Chimera</a> - Highly extensible program for interactive molecular visualization and analysis. <a href=\"https://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/chimera/docs/sourcecode.html\">Source</a> is available.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-13T02:35:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/chimerax/\">ChimeraX</a> - The next-generation molecular visualization program, following UCSF Chimera. Source is available <a href=\"https://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/chimerax/docs/devel/conventions.html\">here</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-13T02:35:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Visulization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nglviewer.org/nglview/latest/\">nglviewer</a> - Interactive molecular graphics for Jupyter notebooks.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-12T09:38:38.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Virtual Machine</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/3D-e-Chem/3D-e-Chem-VM\">3D e-Chem Virtual Machine</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/3D-e-Chem/3D-e-Chem-VM\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">14</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":14,\"repo\":\"3D-e-Chem/3D-e-Chem-VM\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> -</li>","updatedAt":"2020-02-11T12:23:32.000Z"},{"cate