-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/chembl/chembl_beaker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">28</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":28,\"repo\":\"chembl/chembl_beaker\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - <a href=\"http://www.rdkit.org/\">RDKit</a> and <a href=\"https://cactus.nci.nih.gov/osra/\">OSRA</a> in the <a href=\"http://bottlepy.org/docs/dev/\">Bottle</a> on <a href=\"http://www.tornadoweb.org/en/stable/\">Tornado</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Molecular Dynamics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.gromacs.org/\">Gromacs</a> - Molecular dynamics package mainly designed for simulations of proteins, lipids and nucleic acids.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Molecular Dynamics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://openmm.org/\">OpenMM</a> - High performance toolkit for molecular simulation including extensive language bindings for Python, C, C++, and even Fortran.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Molecular Dynamics</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mdtraj/mdtraj\">MDTraj</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mdtraj/mdtraj\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">328</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":328,\"repo\":\"mdtraj/mdtraj\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Analysis of molecular dynamics trajectories.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Courses</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://learncheminformatics.com/\">Learncheminformatics.com</a> - \"Cheminformatics: Navigating the world of chemical data\" courese at Indiana University.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pubchemblog.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/\">PubChem Blog</a> - News, updates and tutorials about <a href=\"https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/\">PubChem</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://chembl.blogspot.tw/\">The ChEMBL-og blog</a> - Stories and news from Computational Chemical Biology Group at <a href=\"https://www.ebi.ac.uk/\">EMBL-EBI</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://chembl.github.io/\">ChEMBL blog</a> - ChEMBL on GitHub.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.steinbeck-molecular.de/steinblog/\">SteinBlog</a> - Blog of <a href=\"http://www.steinbeck-molecular.de/steinblog/index.php/about/\">Christoph Steinbeck</a>, who is the head of cheminformatics and metabolism at the EMBL-EBI.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:49:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/pymol/\">PyMOL</a> - Python-enhanced molecular graphics tool.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://jmol.sourceforge.net/\">Jmol</a> - Browser-based HTML5 viewer and stand-alone Java viewer for chemical structures in 3D.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.ks.uiuc.edu/Research/vmd/\">VMD</a> - Molecular visualization program for displaying, animating, and analyzing large biomolecular systems using 3-D graphics and built-in scripting.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Command Line Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://openbabel.org/wiki/Main_Page\">Open Babel</a> - Chemical toolbox designed to speak the many languages of chemical data.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Docking</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://vina.scripps.edu/\">AutoDock Vina</a> - Molecular docking and virtual screening.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Docking</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/smina/\">smina</a> - Customized <a href=\"http://vina.scripps.edu/\">AutoDock Vina</a> to better support scoring function development and high-performance energy minimization.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>General Purpose</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.rdkit.org/\">RDKit</a> - Collection of cheminformatics and machine-learning software written in C++ and Python.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>General Purpose</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/epam/Indigo\">Indigo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/epam/Indigo\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">153</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":153,\"repo\":\"epam/Indigo\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Universal molecular toolkit that can be used for molecular fingerprinting, substructure search, and molecular visualization written in C++ package, with Java, C#, and Python wrappers.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Format Checking</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mcs07/MolVS\">MolVS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mcs07/MolVS\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">78</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":78,\"repo\":\"mcs07/MolVS\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Molecule validation and standardization based on <a href=\"http://www.rdkit.org/\">RDKit</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-03T22:20:54.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Web APIs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://pubchempy.readthedocs.io\">PubChemPy</a> - Python wrapper for the PubChem PUG REST API.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-02T20:55:27.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Web APIs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://chemspipy.readthedocs.org\">ChemSpiPy</a> - Python wrapper for the ChemSpider API.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-02T20:55:27.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blog.rguha.net/\">So much to do, so little time - Trying to squeeze sense out of chemical data</a> - Bolg of <a href=\"http://blog.rguha.net/?page_id=8\">Rajarshi Guha</a>, who is a research scientist at NIH Center for Advancing Translational Science.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-02T20:55:27.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>See Also</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lmmentel/awesome-python-chemistry\">awesome-python-chemistry</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/lmmentel/awesome-python-chemistry\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">427</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":427,\"repo\":\"lmmentel/awesome-python-chemistry\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Another list focuses on Python stuff related to Chemistry.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-05-02T20:55:27.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/danielecook/Awesome-Bioinformatics","repo":"danielecook/Awesome-Bioinformatics"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/Siddharth11/Colorful","repo":"Siddharth11/Colorful"}},"pageContext":{"repo":"hsiaoyi0504/awesome-cheminformatics","id":"awesomes/github.com/hsiaoyi0504/awesome-cheminformatics","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/danielecook/Awesome-B